{{ja-noun|たたけ|たたげ}}

#{{lb|ja|sort=たたけ|archaic|obsolete}} a [[raccoon dog]]
#* {{RQ:Shin'yaku Kegonkyō Ongi Shiki}}
#*: {{ux|ja|猫狸 [...] ニ又漢云野貍、倭言上尼古、下'''多〻既'''|Cat and raccoon dog, [...] both of them are called {{m|ja||野貍|tr=yari}} in Chinese; the former is called {{m|ja|猫|尼古|tr={{IPAfont|⟨neko<sub>1</sub>⟩}} → neko}} while the latter is called {{m|ja||'''多〻既'''|tr={{IPAfont|⟨tatake<sub>2</sub>⟩}} → '''tatake'''}} in Japanese.}}
# {{lb|ja|archaic|obsolete}} the [[hair]] of a raccoon dog, used for making [[brush]]es
#* '''1445'''-'''1446''', ''{{w|lang=ja|あい嚢鈔|Ainōshō}}''
#*: {{ja-x|'''タゝゲ'''ノ筆ナンド云。'''タゝ毛'''トハ。タヌキノ毛歟。狸ノ字ヲ。'''タゝゲ'''トヨム|'''タゝゲ''' ノ フデ ナンド イフ。 '''タゝゲ''' トハ。 タヌキ ノ ケ カ。 タヌキ ノ ジ ヲ。 '''タゝゲ''' ト ヨム|rom='''Tatage''' no fude nando iu. '''Tatage''' to wa, tanuki no ke ka. Tanuki no ji o, '''tatage''' to yomu|This is a so-called brush [made] of '''''tatage'''''. '''''Tatage''''' [spelled by the character {{ja-l||毛}} meaning "hair"] might mean the hair of a raccoon dog. The {{ja-l||狸}} character for "raccoon dog" is read as '''''tatage'''''.}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=i|たのき}}

Cognate with ''tanuki'' above.

Considered to be a result of irregular [[apophony]] in the medieval times.<ref>{{cite-web|work=狸／貍(タヌキ)とは - コトバンク|url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E7%8B%B8-562006#E7.B2.BE.E9.81.B8.E7.89.88.20.E6.97.A5.E6.9C.AC.E5.9B.BD.E8.AA.9E.E5.A4.A7.E8.BE.9E.E5.85.B8|accessdate=2019-02-12}}</ref>

